data.description:
Peaceful Port Saint Lucie living awaits in this impeccably kept single-family, CBS constructed home with 3 bedrooms, 2 bathrooms and just under 1,500 square feet of living space. Located in the non-HOA and family friendly community of Riverview, this highly desired open and split bedroom floor plan offers brand new flooring, new interior paint and an expansive and fully fenced-in backyard with large screened-in patio!Step inside to be greeted by the newly upgraded gray porcelain plank tile flooring, a freshly painted interior that enhances the home's modern aesthetic and the abundance of natural light coming in from the large front window. To your right you will find your spacious living room that easily flows into the dining area, adorned with sliding glass doors leading out to your oversized covered and screened-in patio. To the left of your dining room is your well-appointed kitchen, boasting white cabinetry with ample storage space, a plethora of counter space, stainless steel appliances, and a convenient double-door pantry. 

Your primary suite offers a luxurious retreat with a double coffered ceiling and dual, separate walk-in closets. The adjoining en-suite features dual sinks for added personal space and a tub/shower combo. On the other side of the home, you have two generously sized guest bedrooms with a shared cabana bath that opens up to the patio. 

Make your way out to your fantastic and fully fenced-in backyard, perfect for enjoying those pink and orange Florida sunsets. Featuring a large, covered and fully screened-in patio as well as a plentiful amount of yard space, with more than enough space to put in a pool! 

Other notable features include a laundry room, a newer AC, which was replaced in 2019, and a new hot water heater installed in 2021. Equipped with hurricane shutters for full hurricane protection.

Explore the neighborhood with easeCrosstown Parkway, just a mile north, provides effortless access to Interstate 95 and the nearby beaches. Residents love the walking path on Crosstown Parkway, and the fantastic community Kiwanis Park is less than a mile away. Convenient amenities surround you, including the Rivergate Publix plaza for groceries and the Port St. Lucie Botanical Gardens, a mere 3.5 miles to the south, hosting seasonal festivities. Boat enthusiasts can launch at the River Park Marina to the north or the St. Lucie River North Fork Ramp to the south. For a quick journey to the heart of Tradition, head west on Crosstown Parkway and south on Village Parkwaya mere 10-mile drive. 

Don't miss the opportunity to make this well-appointed residence your new dream home!
